The paper discusses the recent developments in the area of spacecraft guidance dynamics and control using artificial intelligence techniques such as evolutionary optimization, tree searches, and machine learning including deep learning and reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the application of these techniques in various scenarios, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these techniques in mission designs, which could also place it in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category.
